name: French Martini
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a cocktail shaker with ice and shake for 15 seconds. Strain into a chilled Nick and Nora glass. Note: This cocktail calls for fresh pressed pineapple juice.
source unknown
flavor: Sweeter side of 'martini', kind of like a raspberry grandma candy; does not hide the vodka taste.

name: Lemon Drop
recipe:
Shake all ingredients vigorously in a cocktail shaker for 20 seconds (to help integrate the sugar) and strain into a chilled Nick & Nora glass or Martini Glass. Cut a lemon twist over the glass to add additional oils and drop twist into the glass.

Optionally you can omit the sugar from the drink and rim the glass, but this can create a sticky mess and not integrate as well into the drink.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Flavor profile closely resembling that of a lemon drop candy.

name: Midori Sour
ingredients: [{'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Midori Melon Liqueur'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Sour mix'}, {'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Lemon-Lime Soda'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Luxardo Maraschino Cherry'}]
recipe:
Add all ingredients except for your soda to a cocktail shaker and shake for 15 seconds. Strain into an old fashioned glass over ice. Top with lemon-lime soda and optionally garnish with a maraschino cherry.

Optionally, to 'craft' this cocktail up a bit more, use a half ounce (15ml) egg white to give it a nice white foam with an off-dry finish.
source unknown
flavor: A sweet candy melon with a acidic sour finish with a light carbonation.

name: Pearl Harbor
recipe:
Add ice to a lowball or highball, then add vodka over the ice followed by midori liqueur. Top with the pinepple juice and either stir it (for it to taste great) or leave it layered (to look great).

Want to add a more interesting twist? Add Fee Brothers Rhubarb Bitters for a great spring time flare.
Common Man Cocktails
flavor: Pineapple and melon flavor profile with a refreshing moderate sweetness

name: Sex on the Beach
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a cocktail shaker and shake for 10 seconds. Strain over ice into a tall glass. For true 80's appeal, add cocktail parasole with a flagged cherry and orange. Or, just use an orange slice as your garnish.
source unknown
flavor: Sweet up front and dry in the back, with some red lollipop flavor or watermelon jolly rancher.

name: Slow Comfortable Screw
recipe:
Stir juice, southern comfort and bourbon together with ice until chilled and strain over fresh ice into a highball glass. Float with sloe gin on top (it will sink) and serve.
source unknown
flavor: Taste like freshly squeezed orange juice with a twang of southern comfort sweetness.

name: 3 Dots and a Dash
ingredients: [{'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Martinique Rhum / Rum'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Demerara Rum'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh orange juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Honey Syrup / Mix'}, {'amount': '7.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Falernum Syrup'}, {'amount': '7.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Allspice dram / liqueur'}, {'amount': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Luxardo Maraschino Cherry'}]
recipe:
Combine everything into a blender and blend at high speed for about 5 seconds. Pour into a tall glass and garnish with 3 cherries and a pineapple spear (can also stick the a blade of the pineapple in there). The three cherries are your three "dots" and the spear is the "dash."
Beachbum Berry's Sippin' Safari
garnish: Three Maraschino Cherries and a Pineapple Spear
flavor: Distinct clove-forward flavor, allspice with a nice bite of sour lime and a finishing of warm rum and Martinique funkiness.

name: 5th & Adams
ingredients: [{'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Mezcal'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Ginger Simple Syrup'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Pineapple Juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '2', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': "Peychaud's Bitters"}]
recipe:
All add ingredients to a cocktail shaker with ice and shake for 15 seconds, strain into a chilled coupe glass. Or, double/triple the recipe and put it into a highball glass (because it's just too tasty not to do this).
Bestia: Italian Recipes Created in the Heart of L.A

name: Ancient Mariner
ingredients: [{'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Dark Jamaican rum'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Demerara Rum'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh grapefruit juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Demerara Simple Syrup'}, {'amount': '2', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'Allspice dram / liqueur'}]
recipe:
Build all ingredients in a cocktail shaker with ice and shake for 15 seconds. Dump contents of shaker into a chilled old fashioned glass, garnish and serve!

Bonus points? Score your lime wedge to make it look fancy.
Jeff Berry REMIXED
flavor: Rich molasses notes, a mild to moderate sweetness of allspice and demerara. Refreshing and well balanced.

name: Aruba Ariba
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a shaker with ice and shake for 10 seconds. Strain into a tall glass and garnish.
source unknown
flavor: Light and fruity with coconut, pineapple, cherry and no alcohol kick

name: Bali Bali
ingredients: [{'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Dark Puerto Rican Rum'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Cognac / Brandy'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Light Rum'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Gin'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh orange juice'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Pineapple Juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Falernum Syrup'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Passion fruit syrup'}]
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a cocktail shaker and shake aggressively for 15 seconds and strain over crushed ice into a tiki glass.
Jeff Berry's REMIXED
flavor: Funky rum flavor, classic juicy tiki with mild tart and sour finish

name: Banana Daiquiri
recipe:
Cut and peal half a banana, add banana and all remaining ingredients into blender and blend for 10 seconds or until smooth.

Use your favorite rum for this drink, it makes a difference.
Beachbum Berry REMIXED
flavor: A subtle banana flavor with the focused flavor of your rum breaking right through without being boozy.

name: Barrel o' Rum
ingredients: [{'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Puerto Rican Rum'}, {'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Dark Rum'}, {'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Passion fruit syrup'}, {'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh orange juice'}, {'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh grapefruit juice'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': 'barspoon', 'name': 'Honey Syrup / Mix'}, {'amount': '6', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'Angostura bitters'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Club Soda'}]
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a tin with crushed ice and pulse/blend for 5 seconds (we prefer the Hamilton Beach 730C Classic DrinkMaster Drink Mixer). Dump contents into tiki mug or rum barrel if you have one (especially if it's the Mai Kai rum barrel).
Beachbum Berry's Taboo Table
flavor: Sweet and smooth passion fruit tartness with a mild sour and a good balance of sweet flavor, doesn't feel like four ounces of alcohol. Like a passion fruit lemonade.

name: Beachcomber's Punch
ingredients: [{'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Demerara Rum'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Apricot Brandy'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh grapefruit juice'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': 'dash', 'name': 'Pernod / Absinthe'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': 'dash', 'name': 'Angostura bitters'}]
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a blender and blend for 5 seconds, pour into a champagne flute with additional crushed ice and garnish with mint. We suggest the "dash" of pernod / absinthe utilize about six drops.
Jeff Berry's REMIXED
flavor: Fruity flavors of mild grapefruit, and citrus with a light sweet brown sugar molasses finish

name: Blue Hawaii
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a cocktail shaker with ice and shake aggressively for 12 seconds, strain over crushed ice into a highball glass or hurricane glass. Optionally, blend the cocktail and dump into your glass instead.
source unknown
flavor: Pineapple sweet and light sour finish, spirits are mostly hidden within the beverage

name: Blue Hawaiian
ingredients: [{'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Light Rum'}, {'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Pineapple Juice'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Blue Curacao'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Coco Lopez - Cream of Coconut'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Luxardo Maraschino Cherry'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Pineapple Wedge'}]

Add all ingredients to your cocktail shaker and give it a hard aggressive shake for 20 seconds. Strain over fresh ice into your highball glass, garnish with a pineapple and cherry.

name: Blueberry Mezcal Margarita
recipe:
Puree or Muddle blueberries with fresh lime juice and simple syrup, combine in shaker with bitters and mezcal and shake for 8 to 10 seconds. Dump directly into your old fashioned glass and serve.
source unknown
flavor: A lightly sweet blueberry with a tart sour finish that lingers with smoke

name: Bocce Ball
recipe:
Build all ingredients over ice in a tall glass and stir to integrate. Top with club soda, garnish and serve.
source unknown
flavor: Great almond and orange blend, fairly sweet with a

name: Daiquiri
recipe:
Add all ingredients into your cocktail shaker with ice and shake for 10 seconds. Strain into a chilled coupe glass or over ice into an old fashioned glass and enjoy. Optional garnish would include a lime twist.

We call for "rum", generically, because the daiquiri works with all your favorites from a light rum to an aged rum or even a Demerara rum.
Common Man Cocktails
flavor: Refreshing sour bite with a lingering lime flavor with an overall backbone of beautiful rum.

name: Demerara Dry Float
ingredients: [{'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Demerara Rum'}, {'amount': '7.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Overproof Rum / 151'}, {'amount': '7.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Maraschino Liqueur'}, {'amount': '75.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': 'barspoon', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Passion fruit syrup'}, {'amount': '7.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}]
recipe:
Add all ingredients except the overproof rum together in a cocktail shaker with ice and shake aggressively for 15 seconds. Strain over ice into an old fashioned glass and carefully top (pour over the back of a spoon) with overproof rum.

We suggest an overproof dark rum such as LemonHart 151 for this drink; a clear overproof rum won't look as pretty.
Intoxica by Jeff Berry
flavor: Sweet and Tart with a growing tangy bite that grows on you while also bringing a good sour citrus

name: Doctor Funk
ingredients: [{'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Light Puerto Rican Rum'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': 'barspoon', 'name': 'Pernod / Absinthe'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Grenadine'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Club Soda'}]
recipe:
Shake all ingredients except club soda with ice for 15 seconds. Dump shaker contents into pilsner glass, tiki mug or favorite drinking vessel. Top with club soda, add more ice if needed.
Intoxica by Jeff Berry
flavor: Lemonade and Good & Plenty candy, a light and refreshing sour against black licorice

name: Frozen Mudslide
recipe:
Add two scoops of vanilla ice cream (around 6 ounces) and remaining ingredients to a blender with ice and blend until smooth (roughly 10-15 seconds). Garnish your old fashioned glass with chocolate syrup swirls and pour into your glass.

Optionally add chocolate shavings and whipped cream.
source unknown
flavor: Chocolate milk blended with a cafe latte, great after dinner or before dinner beverage in warm weather.

name: Gin & Jam
ingredients: [{'amount': '37.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Gin'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '7.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Demerara Simple Syrup'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Cranberry Jam'}, {'amount': '2', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'Mexican Mole Bitters'}]
recipe:

Montana's Trail House Restaurant - Brooklyn, NY
flavor: Sweet up front, dry in the back with notes of juniper pairing with a fruity cranberry.

name: Gin & Orange Special
recipe:
Add all ingredients over ice into a tall glass and serve. Simple! The key to the flavors of this cocktail is the use of fresh pressed orange juice, it just doesn't compare to bottled OJ.
source unknown
flavor: A juicy flavorful citrus against a subtle gin that's easy to taste and a great pool side beverage. The gin does hide pretty well however.

name: Gin Gin Mule
ingredients: [{'amount': '52.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'London Dry Gin'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Ginger Beer'}, {'amount': '8', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Mint Leaves'}]
recipe:
Muddle simple syrup, lime juice, and 8 mint leaves in the bottom of your shaker tin. Add gin and top with ice, then shake for 15 seconds. Double strain (with tea strainer to remove any mint) over fresh ice in a tall glass. Top with ginger beer and garnish with a fresh new mint sprig. Server with a straw.
New York Cocktails: An Elegant Collection of over 100 Recipes Inspired by the Big Apple (City Cocktails)
flavor: Minty sweetness with a hint of backend ginger flavor

name: Mayan Mule #2
ingredients: [{'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Chili Steeped Tequila'}, {'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh orange juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Ginger Beer'}]
recipe:
Rim glass with sugar, cinnamon and coco and set aside. Add all ingredients except ginger beer to a cocktail shaker with ice and shake for 15 seconds. Strain over ice into a highball glass and top with ginger beer.

Chili Steeped Tequila: Roast a habanero pepper or two, and peel of the skin once it crisps a bit. Take the skinless habanero and soak them in tequila (5-6 ounces or so) for 30 minutes. Use that for the tequila called for in this cocktail.

For rim: add demerara sugar, cinnamon and coco to a bowl and mix to integrate. Use that as your rim garnish. Wet the rim with lime juice.
source unknown
garnish: Cinnamon, Demerara Sugar and Coco rim
flavor: Hot and spicy fire, chocolate, tequila, spice and acidity all wrapped in more spicy heat!

recipe:
Add all the ingredients to a shaker and fill with ice. Shake for 15 seconds and strain into a chilled cocktail glass. Garnish with a cherry if desired.
Hugo Ensslin
flavor: Approachable classic cocktail with complicated herbal notes, violet/flowery mid-palate which plays well against the juniper notes. In some ways, "tastes like purple."

name: Bay Breeze
recipe:
Shake all ingredients vigorously in a cocktail shaker for 10 seconds and strain over fresh ice into a tall glass and garnish.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Sweet pineapple paired against tart cranberry, light on alcohol. Tropical flavor profile.

name: Bees Knees
recipe:
Shake all ingredients vigorously in a cocktail shaker for 10 seconds and strain into a chilled Nick & Nora glass and garnish with a twist of lemon.

To fashion yourself some honey syrup, we suggest adding 1-part water to 1-part honey (clover honey if you have it) and stir them to dilute. If your honey is very thick or hard, heat your water first to help soften the honey in the mix. Or, just buy a bottle of pre-made honey mix.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Lemon Centric flavor profile, muted honey sweetness with gin botanicals.

name: Betsy Ross Cocktail
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a mixing glass with ice and stir until chilled (usually around 2 minutes). Strain into a chilled coupe/martini glass and serve.
source unknown
flavor: A boozy number that combines flavors of cognac and port, leaning on the sweet side of potent alcohol-forward flavor. Look for dry curacao / orange liqueur to keep down the sweet notes.

name: Bijou Cocktail
recipe:
Add ice to your Nick and Nora glass (our coupe/martini) with water and set aside. Add all ingredients to a mixing glass with ice and stir for around two minutes. Dump cold water out of your glass and strain cocktail into your now chilled vessel.

Garnish with an olive or real maraschino cherry and serve.

Note: We have chose Harry Johnson's original recipe over Dale Degroffs re-balance because of the stronger chartreuse flavor profile without the lighter "watered down" feel of the additional gin.
1900 Harry Johnson's Bartenders Manual
flavor: A bright chartreuse and and gin vibrancy with a good deal of potency. A balance of botanicals and herbs.

name: Blood & Sand
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a shaker and shake for 12 seconds, strain into a coupe, old fashioned glass (on ice), or Nick & Nora glass, whichever you prefer. Flame an orange peel over the beverage, rub the peel on the edge of the glass, and drop it into the drink.
source unknown
flavor: Peaty scotch notes mixed with vermouth and a light cherry finish

name: Boulevardier
recipe:
Chill your old fashioned glass with ice and water and set aside. Add all ingredients with ice to a mixing glass and stir for 2 minutes. Dump your chilled water from the old fashioned glass and strain into chilled glass.

Rub an orange twist around the rim of the glass and drop into the glass. Serve.
Harry MacElhone / Harry's New York Bar
flavor: Slightly sweeter than a negroni that brings the rye intensity followed by a campari bitter bite that lingers.

name: Brooklyn
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a mixing glass and stir for up to 2 minutes until well chilled. Strain into a chilled martini glass, coupe or nick & nora and serve.

The original recipe calls for Amer Picon or angostura bitters, but the most reasonable substitution is orange bitters because it is widely available.
source unknown
flavor: A dry forward flavor with a subtle rye to add a mild sweetness, the maraschino liqueur is quite muted but ties the flavors together.

name: Caipiroska / Capivodka
recipe:
Put lime quarters in the bottom of an Old Fashioned glass and add sugar over the lime quarters. Muddle the lime with the sugar using a muddler as this will score the lime skin against the sugar grains and extract additional oils from the skin.

Once the limes are crushed into the sugar grains, fill the glass three quarters full with crushed ice then fill with vodka and give it a stir.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Sweet lime and light flavor of ethanol, slight limeade flavor

name: Cape Codder
recipe:
Build over ice in a tall glass and garnish! We suggest cranberry juice cocktail for this drink, one with a bit of sugar to tame the tart (not fresh pressed cranberries).
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Cranberry sweet and tart with a slight kick

name: Chartreuse Martini
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a cocktail shaker and shake for 15 seconds and strain into a chilled nick & nora glass or martini glass.
source unknown
flavor: Herbal with muted anise flavor, lightly dry vermouth finish

name: Chicago South Side
ingredients: [{'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'London Dry Gin'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}, {'amount': '7', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'Angostura bitters'}, {'amount': '10', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Mint Leaves'}]
recipe:
Shake all ingredients vigorously in a cocktail shaker (including mint) for 10 seconds and double strain into a chilled coupe glass, garnish with 1 mint leaf.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Lovely aromatic flavor of trade spices, gin botanicals and acidity. Just a great drink.

name: Chrysanthemum
recipe:
Stir all ingredients in a mixing glass until chilled (up to 2 minutes) and strain into a chilled coupe glass and garnish. Use a good vermouth on this cocktail.
Hugo Ensslin
flavor: Flavorful vermouth pairs with the sweetness of Benedictine; floral and well balanced with a muted black licorice finish

name: Clover Club
ingredients: [{'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'London Dry Gin'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Raspberry Syrup'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Egg White'}]
recipe:
Dry shake all ingredients (without ice) for 15 seconds, add ice and shake again for 10 seconds; strain into a chilled coupe glass, garnish with 3 raspberries on a spear.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Raspberry sweetness mingled with floral juniper with a light dry citrus mid-palate that finishes sweet and silky with raspberries and gin.

name: Corpse Reviver #2
recipe:
Add absinthe to chilled coupe and swirl it around the glass and discard remaining absinthe (known as a "rinse"). Build remaining ingredients in a cocktail shaker with ice and shake for 15 seconds. Strain into chilled coupe and serve.
source unknown
flavor: An herbal sour bite that will wake you up with a bit of aromatic gin/juniper aroma with a bit of a fennel mid-palate flavor.

name: Dirty Martini
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a mixing glass and stir for 30 seconds to 2 minutes. Strain into a chilled nick and nora glass and garnish with one or three olives.
source unknown
flavor: Bright gin flavor against a light salty brine, yet still gin forward with an off-dry finish.

name: Gin & Tonic
recipe:
In a tall glass, pour gin over cubes of ice. Squeeze a lime wedge and drop it into the glass followed by tonic water and serve.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Light and refreshing juniper notes with a creeping tonic bite that finishes clean.

name: Gin and Juice
recipe:
Add ice to a tall glass, add gin and juice. You can select your own "juice", but our recipe is slightly more unique than a simple greyhound (grapefruit juice).
source unknown
flavor: Flavorful citrus juice blend with muted / hidden gin flavor

name: Gin Fix
ingredients: [{'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'London Dry Gin'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Rich simple syrup'}]
recipe:
Shake all ingredients vigorously in a cocktail shaker for 10 seconds and strain into a chilled Nick & Nora glass or martini glass. Garnish with a orange slice and serve.
Home Cocktail Menu

name: Gin Fizz
ingredients: [{'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'London Dry Gin'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Club Soda'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Egg White'}]
recipe:
Dry shake all ingredients except club soda (without ice) for 15 seconds, add ice and shake again for 10 seconds; strain over ice into a lowball glass. Top with Club Soda. Serve immediately.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Smooth and silky lemon flavor with muted notes of juniper and a dry finish

name: Gin Gimlet
recipe:
Shake all ingredients vigorously in a cocktail shaker for 10 seconds and strain into a chilled Nick & Nora glass and garnish.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Simple taste of gin and lime with more tart than sour.

name: Gin Martini
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a mixing glass with ice and stir for 30 seconds. Using a julep strainer (or hawthorne strainer if it fits), strain into a chilled Nick & Nora glass. Optional olive (or 3) as garnish.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Potent gin botanical attack, fortified wine and an off-dry finish

name: Greyhound
recipe:
Build over ice in a tall glass and serve. If there is extra room in the glass, you can always double the ratio to fill out the glass.

Prior to 1945, in the United States at least, most cocktails contained gin instead of vodka so many classics like the Greyhound were gin-based utilizing similar ratios.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: A tart grapefruit flavor profile with mild potency hidden well in the juice.

name: Hanky Panky
ingredients: [{'amount': '52.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'London Dry Gin'}, {'amount': '52.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Sweet Vermouth'}, {'amount': '7.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh orange juice'}, {'amount': '2', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'Fernet Branca'}]
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a mixing glass with ice and stir until chilled (usually up to 2 minutes). Strain into a chilled martini glass, add an orange twist, and serve.
Ada Coleman
flavor: A smooth sweetness, brown sugar that moves into Eucalypus, citrus with forward-vermouth finish. Very manhattan like in flavor design.

name: Harvey Wallbanger
recipe:
Add ice to your tall glass and follow it up with vodka and fresh squeezed orange juice. Float Galliano on top, add a straw and garnish. Serve.
source unknown
flavor: Imagine the screwdriver with a bit of herbal sweetness. Yep, orange juice, spirit and a hint of black licorice in the finish.

name: Hemingway Daiquiri
ingredients: [{'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Light Rum'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Maraschino Liqueur'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh grapefruit juice'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}]
recipe:
Add all ingredients to an iced cocktail shaker and shake for 15 seconds. Strain into a chilled coupe/cocktail glass and serve.

Also been called Daiquiri #3.
source unknown
flavor: Light sour lime against herbal maraschino sweetness and a mild yet muted rum flavor. Easy to drink, good balance.

name: Hot Toddy
recipe:
Prepare your mug by adding additional boiling water to your mug to warm it up quickly. Once warm/hot empty your mug and add lemon juice, honey bourbon (or regular bourbon) and top with hot water.

To prepare a studded lemon peel, cut your peel and poke 3 whole cloves through the peel and add it to your drink. Add a cinnamon stick and serve.

If you do not have honey bourbon we suggest your favorite bourbon and, if you desire honey, add a bar spoon of honey to your finished drink and stir (helps to remove it from the spoon as well).
Common Man Cocktails
garnish: Studded Lemon Peel and Cinnamon Stick
flavor: Warm citrus, alcohol (especially from the hot fumes) and honey, just as one would expect.

name: Lion's Tail
ingredients: [{'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Bourbon Whiskey'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Allspice dram / liqueur'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': 'barspoon', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}, {'amount': '2', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'Angostura bitters'}]
recipe:
Add all your ingredients to a cocktail shaker with ice and give it a hardy shake for 15 seconds, strain into a coupe glass or nick and nora glass. Garnish with a slice of orange or other citrus.
The Café Royal Cocktail Book (1937)
flavor: An off-dry flavor of bourbon, allspice finish that's well balanced with acidity.

name: Madras
recipe:
Build over ice in a tall glass and garnish with an orange wheel and serve. Alternatively, you can layer the ingredients with orange juice, cranberry juice, and a vodka float to give it a pretty presentation (although slightly disjointed taste).
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Tropical like flavor with beautiful citrus paired with tart cranberry and lightly sweet pressed oranges.

name: Manhattan
recipe:
Add all the ingredients into a mixing glass halfway filled with ice. Stir until well-chilled and strain into a chilled coupe or martini glass. Garnish with a cherry.
source unknown
flavor: Mild sweetness with a musky rye flavor and a hint of fortified wine

name: Margarita
recipe:
Add all ingredients into your cocktail shaker with ice. Shake for 15 seconds and strain over ice into an old fashioned glass and garnish. Optionally, rim your glass with salt.

For a slightly sweeter experience, utilize crushed ice to chill down the cocktail faster and colder. For a more sour experience, tailer back your agave nectar by a quarter ounce (or 7.5ml).
Common Man Cocktails
flavor: Agave forward flavor, mingled with citrus and bright tequila notes.

name: Martinez
recipe:
Shake all ingredients vigorously in a cocktail shaker for 10 seconds and strain into a chilled coupe glass.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Stong potent start mixed with orange and subtle juniper with a mid-palate and finish that lingers bitter, tart and powerful.

name: Mojito
ingredients: [{'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Light Rum'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '2', 'unit': 'barspoons', 'name': 'Casters sugar (superfine sugar)'}, {'amount': '12', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Mint Leaves'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Club Soda'}]
recipe:
Add your lime wedges and sugar to your tall glass, and muddle them together. Slap ('spank') your mint and add it into your glass over your muddled lime and sugar. Give it a gentle muddle without tearing your mint.

Add crushed ice over the ingredients until you're about halfway up the glass. Then top with light rum and integrate the ingredients by stirring with a bar spoon.

Top with additional crushed ice and top with club soda. Add your garnish and a straw and serve.
source unknown
flavor: Light and refreshing sweet mint and sour lime bite with a light rum backend flavor.

name: Monte Carlo
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a mixing glass with ice and stir for 30 seconds to a minute, strain over fresh ice into a lowball glass, or straight up into a coupe glass.
source unknown
flavor: Light notes of honey meets spicy notes of rye for a delicious balance

name: Moscow Mule
recipe:
Build in a copper mug (for tradition) or old fashioned glass if no mug is available and add your garnish.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Spicy ginger zing with a refreshing citrus flavor, not too complex but great for pool side, hot weather and parties.

name: New York Sour
ingredients: [{'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Bourbon Whiskey'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Egg White'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Red Wine'}]
recipe:
Add all ingredients but red wine to a cocktail shaker without ice and dry shake aggressively for 15 seconds. Add ice to your shaker and shake again for 15 seconds and strain over ice into an old fashioned glass. Float red wine on top and serve.
source unknown
flavor: Smooth flavor, dry finish. Lightly fruity red wine against oak-driven flavor profile with a nice acidity.

name: Old Fashioned
recipe:
Add sugar cube to an old fashioned glass and soak it with bitters of your choice (we prefer Boy Drinks World Walnut Bitters but you can use Angostura as well).

Once you've added your bitters to the sugar, muddle the sugar cube into the glass with a muddler and then pour your rye (or bourbon) into the glass. Add a couple cubes of ice and stir to dilute ice down a bit and integrate the bitter sugars.

Optionally, garnish with an orange wheel and maraschino cherry.
source unknown
flavor: Forward rye flavor with muted bitters; simple.

name: Planter's Punch
ingredients: [{'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Dark Rum'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh orange juice'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Pineapple Juice'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Grenadine'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}, {'amount': '4', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'Angostura bitters'}]
recipe:
Add all ingredients into a cocktail shaker with ice and shake for 15 seconds and strain into a chilled coupe glass. Use your favorite dark rum for this recipe, we love Plantation Original Dark for this build.
source unknown
flavor: Foamy Fruity flavors mingled with molasses forward dark rum with a juicy tropical loveliness.

name: Ramos Gin Fizz
ingredients: [{'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Gin'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Heavy Cream'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '3', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'Orange Flower Water'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Egg White'}, {'amount': 'null', 'unit': 'null', 'name': 'Club Soda'}]

Add all ingredients except your ice and club soda to a shaker and shake it without ice (dry shake) for 15 seconds as aggressive as possible. Add ice and shake for 15 seconds or more and strain into a collins glass without ice. Top with club soda and serve.
source unknown
flavor: Pure herbal gin and citrus forward flavor and aroma

name: Rob Roy
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a mixing glass with ice and stir until chilled (usually about 2 minutes). Strain into a chilled coupe or cocktail glass.
Waldorf Astoria
flavor: Spirit forward flavor, lots of scotch comes through from start to finish; slight peaty smoke (or heavy if you use an Islay Scotch)

name: Rum Runner
ingredients: [{'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Pineapple Juice'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh orange juice'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Chambord / Raspberry Liqueur'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Banana liqueur'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Light Rum'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Aged Rum'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': 'splash', 'name': 'Grenadine'}]
recipe:
Add everything into a cocktail shaker and shake it all for 10 to 15 seconds and strain into a tall glass. Garnish with an orange wheel.
source unknown
flavor: Raspberry candy with a little banana filling; This is a potent number, you can taste the alcohol.

name: Rusty Nail
recipe:
Add both ingredients to an old fashioned glass and stir. You can serve with ice or "neat" depending on your preference (but chill the glass if you're going to serve it neat).
source unknown
flavor: Scotch with honey like sweetness of Drambuie.

name: Salty Dog
ingredients: [{'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'London Dry Gin'}, {'amount': '120.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh grapefruit juice'}, {'amount': '4', 'unit': 'barspoons', 'name': 'Course Sea Salt'}]
recipe:
Rim a tall glass with salt and set aside. Shake gin and grapefruit juice vigorously in a cocktail shaker for 10 seconds and strain over ice into your tall rimmed glass. Garnish with a quarter slice of grapefruit and serve.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Light flavor of juniper and lightly tart fleshy grapefruit flavor.

name: Sazerac
recipe:
Add absinthe to your chilled old fashioned glass, and move it around the base of the glass and along the sides (known as a "rinse") and pour the remaining out. Set glass aside.

Muddle sugar and bitters in a mixing glass and then add rye whiskey. Add ice and stir to chill down for about 2 minutes. Strain into rinsed old fashioned glass; use lemon twist to express oils over drink and on glass. Discard lemon twist.

Note: It's not a mistake, a sazerac isn't served on ice. Just a chilled old fashioned glass.
Antoine Amedie Peychaud
flavor: Spicy rye with a backend hint of anise/fennel and a slight sweetness.

name: Screwdriver
recipe:
Build over ice in a tall glass and add your garnish. Works best with fresh squeezed orange juice.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Light and refreshing orange juice flavor with a mild kick

name: Sea Breeze
recipe:
Build over ice in a tall glass and garnish with lime wedge and serve. Fresh grapefruit juice will give this a smooth mild tartness vs. a more aggressive tartness from bottled grapefruit juice.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: A tart bite, mild sour with an off-dry finish; vodka does not play a big role.

name: Sidecar
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a cocktail shaker with ice and shake for 15 seconds. Strain over ice into an old fashioned or into a chilled (no ice) nick & nora glass and garnish.

The recipe balance can be done in many ways and has been over the years. You can also try a 2:1:1 balance or even a 3:2:2 ratio of strong to sweet/sour.
Harry's ABC of Mixing Cocktails
flavor: A driving lemon and brandy/cognac forward flavor, with a mild sweet and a citrus sour. Not as much brandy as some recipe ratios propose.

name: Singapore Sling
ingredients: [{'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Gin'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Cherry Heering Liqueur'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Cointreau'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Benedictine'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Grenadine'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': 'dash', 'name': 'Angostura bitters'}, {'amount': '120.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Pineapple Juice'}]
recipe:
Add ingredients to a shaker tin with ice and shake for 10 seconds and dump entire shaker contents into a hurricane glass and serve.

Note:If you don't have hurricane glasses, use a standard highball glass for this recipe. Owning a hurricane glass just for this (and potentially a hurricane cocktail) may be overkill.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Tropical flavors of almond, brown sugar, cherry, pineapple and an array of sweetness.

name: Sloe Gin Fizz
ingredients: [{'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Sloe Gin'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '7.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Egg White'}, {'amount': 'null', 'unit': 'null', 'name': 'Club Soda'}]
recipe:
Add all but club soda into your cocktail shaker. Because we're using egg white, dry shake (with no ice) the cocktail aggressively for 20 seconds. Add ice cubes and shake for an additional 15 seconds and strain into your tall glass and top with 2 oz - 3 oz Club Soda.

Optionally pour over ice if you want a slightly colder beverage.
source unknown
flavor: Dry berry flavor, brown sugar with a light off-dry and tart finish.

name: Southside
recipe:
Shake all ingredients vigorously in a cocktail shaker (including mint) for 10 seconds and double strain into a chilled coupe glass and garnish with a single mint leaf.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: A sour-forward gin flavored design with subtle mint flavor.

name: Tequila Sour
ingredients: [{'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Reposado Tequila'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '7.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Agave nectar'}, {'amount': '3', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'Bittercube Chipotle Cacao Bitters'}, {'amount': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Egg White'}]

Add all ingredients into a cocktail shaker and dry shake (without ice) aggressively for 15 seconds. Add ice and shake again for 15 seconds then double strain into an old fashioned glass (ice optional). Add three dots of bitters for presentation and serve.
source unknown
flavor: Lightly dry citrus meets agave with cinnamon spice, cacao and lingering tequila.

name: The Dorchester
ingredients: [{'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'London Dry Gin'}, {'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lime juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh grapefruit juice'}, {'amount': '7.5', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Maraschino Liqueur'}]
recipe:
Shake all ingredients vigorously in a cocktail shaker for 10 seconds and strain into a chilled Nick & Nora glass or martini glass. Garnish with a grapefruit twist and serve.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Floral forward herbal flavor, mid-palate citrus acidity, finishing of juniper, sweet herbaceous linger.

name: The Last Word
recipe:
Add all ingredients to a cocktail shaker with ice and shake for 15 seconds. Strain into a chilled coupe or nick & nora glass.
Rediscovered by Murray Stenson, Zig Zag Cafe
flavor: A balanced herbal forward cocktail that doesn't lean towards sour, and has hints of sweetness.

name: The Vesper
recipe:
Chill a large coupe glass with water and ice; set aside.

Add cocktail ingredients to a cocktail shaker with ice and shake aggressively for 10 seconds. Dump ice and water from your glass and double strain (to remove ice shards) contents of the shaker into your chilled glass.

Garnish with a lemon peel and serve.

If you can't find Lillet Blanc, you can substitute Cocchi Americano.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Strong and direct gin with a hint of bitter bite; not for the weak at heart.

name: Tom Collins
ingredients: [{'amount': '45.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Old Tom Gin'}, {'amount': '30.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Simple syrup'}, {'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Club Soda'}]
recipe:
Build over ice in a tall glass and top with soda water and gently stir; garnish with a lemon slice, serve.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Refreshing yet sour start with a mildly sweet tart gin ending with bubbly citrus and a lingering sour lemon

name: Vodka Collins
recipe:
Build over ice in a tall glass and top with soda water and gently stir; garnish with a lemon slice and cherry, serve. Vodka is a rather flavorless core spirit so consider club soda over seltzer water in this drink to give this cocktail a bit of added nuance.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Light and refreshing lemonade like appeal, with a kick of alcohol in the finish.

name: Whiskey Sour
recipe:
Add ingredients to a shaker tin with ice and shake for 10 seconds. Strain into a chilled lowball glass and serve. Egg White is optional (technically that makes it a Boston Sour, but it's a fantastic edition).

If using egg whites, use the dry shake method (shake all ingredients without ice aggressively for 20-seconds then add ice and shake for 15 seconds).
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: A mingling of citrus and whiskey and a silky smooth texture that ends off-dry.

name: White Lady
ingredients: [{'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'London Dry Gin'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Orange Liqueur'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Fresh lemon juice'}, {'amount': '15.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Egg White'}]
recipe:
Dry shake all ingredients (without ice) for 15 seconds, add ice and shake again for 10 seconds; strain into a chilled coupe glass.
Home Cocktail Menu
flavor: Smooth timid start of citrus, growing juniper mid-palate mingled with lemon with a dry citrus finish.

name: White Russian
recipe:
Build over ice in an old fashioned glass, adding your cream/milk/half-and-half last so it builds a neat presentation. Optionally, add nutmeg to the top as a garnish.

name: Uncle Angelo's Eggnog
ingredients: [{'amount': '120.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Bourbon Whiskey'}, {'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Spiced Rum'}, {'amount': '60.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'White granulated sugar'}, {'amount': '480.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Whole Milk'}, {'amount': '240.0', 'unit': 'ml', 'name': 'Heavy Cream'}, {'amount': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Whole Egg'}]
recipe:
Split Yolk and egg white into separate bowls.
Beat egg yolks and fold in 3 tsp of sugar as you beat.
Stir in milk, heavy cream, bourbon, and rum into your egg yolk mixture. Add a few pinches of fresh grated nutmeg as well.
Using a drink mixer or separate bowl/whisk, beat your egg whites and remaining sugar until they form a soft peak.
Fold a third of the egg whites into the yolk mixture with a spoon.
Pour into your serving glasses, top with a bit more egg white and a little additional nutmeg.
Service around 6 drinks in single recipe "serving."
Note: Use real sugar, not simple syrup (2 oz of sugar equals 1/4 cup)
Dale Degroff
flavor: Eggnog with a warm nutmeg and light alcohol warmth, fantastic creaminess

name: Spanish Coffee
recipe:
Rim mug with a thick later of sugar using lime juice or water to stick sugar to the rim (inside and out.) Once the sugar is stuck and slightly solidified add 151 to your mug along side orange liqueur / triple sec.

Now, light your liquid on fire and tip your mug carefully so it begins to caramelize the sugars along the inside of the rim. Continue to roll along the sides so the flame licks the sugar rim and warms it.

Add a few dashes of nutmeg (so it lights up and sparks). Add kahlua, which will put out the fire (or, put it out on your own if it doesn't go out.) Then top with coffee. Float whipped cream on top.
Jeffery Morgenthaler

name: Absinthe Drip Cocktail (French method)
recipe: POUR absinthe into glass. PLACE cube of sugar on a slotted absinthe spoon resting across the top of the glass. Using an absinthe fountain (or a bottle of chilled mineral water with a small hole in the cap), DRIP iced water over the sugar so it dissolves and drips into the glass. Traditionally the same amount of water is added as absinthe, but full-strength absinthe requires more dilution - Keep dripping until absinthe louches (turns milky white). Add ice, stir and serve.
content: Patience is a virtue. Slow dripping of the water is essential to dissolve the entire sugar cube and give the drink enough sweetness to balance the absinthe.

name: Bird of Paradise Gin Fizz
ingredients: [{'name': "Hayman's Old Tom Gin", 'amount': '60', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Lime juice (freshly squeezed)', 'amount': '30', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Raspberry (framboise) sugar syrup', 'amount': '15', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Orange flower/blossom water', 'amount': '3', 'unit': 'drop'}, {'name': 'Pasteurised egg white (or aquafaba)', 'amount': '20', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Thomas Henry Soda Water', 'amount': 'Top up with', 'unit': 'Topupwith'}]
recipe:
SHAKE first 5 ingredients with ice and strain back into shaker. DRY SHAKE (without ice) and slowly pour 2/3rds of the contents of the shaker from a higher than normal height into a chilled empty glass (no ice in glass) while simultaneously pouring soda with your other hand. The cocktail and soda should form a single stream of liquid falling into the glass.

As when pouring a Guinness, to achieve a perfect head on a fizz, the cocktail should be left to settle for at least a minute before topping off with what remains in the shaker. Ideally, during the settling period, the glass should be placed in a glass froster/fridge/freezer. As the final contents of the shaker are poured into the glass so the head should rise like a souffle.
content: A Gin Fizz with pleasing rich raspberry notes, discovered by Charles H. Baker at the Strangers Club in Panama.

name: Berry Caipirinha
recipe:
1. Cut lime in half (from pole to pole) and then slice one of the halves into eight 3-4mm thick half-moon shaped segments and drop into the base of a robust rocks glass.

2. Add 3 bar spoons caster sugar (or ½oz / 15ml sugar syrup 2:1) and MUDDLE.

3. Add mixed berries and MUDDLE some more.

4. When sure fruit juice is fully extracted and the sugar dissolved, transfer the muddled fruit and sugar into serving glass (preferably a 30cl / 10oz highball glass).

5. POUR cachaça (stored in the freezer) into the rocks glass (used to muddle) and swirl to rinse glass before pouring cachaça into serving glass. STIR to ensure all ingredients are well mixed.

6. Crack (rather than crush) four to five large ice cubes using an Ice Tapper and drop into serving glass. STIR before topping with more ice and serve with a stirrer (but no straws).
garnish: Stirrer (spoon, wooden lolly stick or stick cut from sugar cane)

name: Ramos Gin Fizz
ingredients: [{'name': "Hayman's Old Tom Gin", 'amount': '60', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Lemon juice (freshly squeezed)', 'amount': '15', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Lime juice (freshly squeezed)', 'amount': '15', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': "Sugar syrup 'rich' (2 sugar to 1 water, 65.0°brix)", 'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Orange flower/blossom water', 'amount': '1.25', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Vanilla extract (optional)', 'amount': '3', 'unit': 'drop'}, {'name': 'Pasteurised egg white (or aquafaba)', 'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Single cream / half-and-half', 'amount': '22.5', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Thomas Henry Soda Water', 'amount': 'Top up with', 'unit': 'Topupwith'}]
recipe:
SHAKE first 8 ingredients with ice and strain back into shaker. DRY SHAKE (without ice) and slowly pour 2/3rds of the contents of the shaker from a higher than normal height into a chilled empty glass (no ice in glass) while simultaneously pouring soda with your other hand. The cocktail and soda should form a single stream of liquid falling into the glass.

As when pouring a Guinness, to achieve a perfect head on a Ramos Gin Fizz, the cocktail should be left to settle for at least a minute before topping off with what remains in the shaker. Ideally, during the settling period, the glass should be placed in a glass froster/fridge/freezer. As the final contents of the shaker are poured into the glass so the head should rise like a souffle.

Some Ramos Gin Fizz recipes, and indeed Henry Charles Ramos' original recipe, call for old tom gin (also our preference), in which case you may need to reduce the amount of sugar syrup depending on your old tom, personal tastes and citrus fruit.
garnish: Quarter orange wheel on rim (& optional mint sprig)

name: Chicago Fizz
ingredients: [{'name': 'Dark/black/blackstrap rum', 'amount': '30', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Tawny port', 'amount': '30', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Lemon juice (freshly squeezed)', 'amount': '15', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': "Sugar syrup 'rich' (2 sugar to 1 water, 65.0°brix)", 'amount': '7.5', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Pasteurised egg white (or aquafaba)', 'amount': '15', 'unit': 'ml'}, {'name': 'Thomas Henry Soda Water', 'amount': '30', 'unit': 'ml'}]
recipe:
SHAKE first 5 ingredients with ice and strain back into shaker. DRY SHAKE (without ice) and slowly pour 2/3rds of the contents of the shaker from a higher than normal height into a chilled empty glass (no ice in glass) while simultaneously pouring soda with your other hand. The cocktail and soda should form a single stream of liquid falling into the glass.

As when pouring a Guinness, to achieve a perfect head on a fizz, the cocktail should be left to settle for at least a minute before topping off with what remains in the shaker. Ideally, during the settling period, the glass should be placed in a glass froster/fridge/freezer. As the final contents of the shaker are poured into the glass so the head should rise like a souffle.
content: Rum character shines, distinguishing this from lesser fizzes.

Spicy sugar syrup
To make your own festive spice syrup: Stir half a cup of hot water and half a cup of sugar in a pan until sugar is dissolved. Add 1 cracked cinnamon stick, ½ a split vanilla pod and 1 teaspoon of cracked Szechuan peppers. Cover for 15 minutes then strain and cool liquid. If using this syrup in the recipe below then use 12.5ml.
